    "body": "<!--\r\n**Note:**\r\n- Do not use the bug and feature tracker for support requests. Use the `cython-users` mailing list instead.\r\n- Did you search for similar issues already? Please do, it helps to save us precious time that we otherwise could not invest into development.\r\n- Did you try the latest master branch or pre-release? It might already have what you want to report. Also see the [Changelog](https://github.com/cython/cython/blob/master/CHANGES.rst) regarding recent changes.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\nPure python version of\r\n```cython\r\ncdef int spam() except +\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\nSome ideas:\r\nAdd `cppcheck` kwarg to `cython.exceptval`, if it's `True`, then this will translate to adding `+` to `except` and if the first argument of `cython.exceptval` is callable then `cppcheck` will be set to `True`(debatable).\r\nExamples:\r\n```python\r\n@cython.cfunc\r\n@cython.exceptval(cppcheck=True)\r\ndef spam() -> cython.int\r\n```\r\n->\r\n```cython\r\ncdef int spam() except +\r\n```\r\n---\r\n```python\r\n@cython.cfunc\r\n@cython.exceptval(check=True, cppcheck=True)\r\ndef spam() -> cython.int\r\n```\r\n->\r\n```cython\r\ncdef int spam() except +*\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n```python\r\n@cython.cfunc\r\n@cython.exceptval(MemoryError)\r\ndef spam() -> cython.int\r\n```\r\n->\r\n```cython\r\ncdef int spam() except +MemoryError\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n```python\r\n@cython.cfunc\r\n@cython.exceptval(MemoryError, cppcheck=True)\r\ndef spam() -> cython.int\r\n```\r\n->\r\n```cython\r\ncdef int spam() except +MemoryError\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nAnd this probably should fail\r\n\r\n```python\r\n@cython.cfunc\r\n@cython.exceptval(MemoryError, check=True)\r\ndef spam() -> cython.int\r\n```\r\nAs this code does\r\n\r\n```cython\r\ncdef int spam() except +MemoryError*\r\n```",
